# Phoenix Bot — line-ending normalization (P21, 2026-04-20)
#
# All text files stored with LF in repo and checked out as LF.
# Windows-native tooling (cmd.exe, NinjaScript, PowerShell) accepts LF;
# empirically verified across the current repo (all .cs/.bat files have
# been LF for months and work fine against NT8 / cmd).
#
# If you edit .cs files directly in NT8's NinjaScript editor (which saves
# CRLF on disk by default), git will normalize back to LF on commit —
# expected and harmless. Visible as "modified" in `git status` until
# committed.
#
# Applied alongside `core.autocrlf false` to prevent the checkout-time
# LF→CRLF conversion that accumulated 137 working-tree-CRLF files across
# the roadmap-v4 + Option B + verification sprints.

* text=auto eol=lf

# ── Binary files — never munge EOLs ──────────────────────────────────
*.png    binary
*.jpg    binary
*.jpeg   binary
*.gif    binary
*.ico    binary
*.pdf    binary
*.sqlite binary
*.db     binary
*.parquet binary
*.pyc    binary
*.pyo    binary
*.zip    binary
*.nt8bk  binary
